    <note>Cheng(1) Kan(2) [26399] He was Junqi fushi or assistant commisioner for armaments under the Southern Tang. His grandson, Zhao(2) [26401] was responsible for increasing the output of iron, and his great grandson, Shuliang [26402] (q.v.), was an military official in charge of the Cihu ironworks (Jian Cihu Du Tieye wu), and the family was a member of an illustrious lineage (zhuxing) of Daye. There can be little doubt but that this was an industrialist lineage.</note>
